column12: HOMODYNE RECEIVE ARCHITECTURE IN A SPATIAL ESTIMATION SYSTEM
column13: A method of detection of transmitted light reflected from an environment, an optical system for spatial estimation and associated components are described. Outgoing light is provided for spatial estimation, which may include wavelength channels directed by a beam director. A local oscillator signal is used in the detection of reflected light of the wavelength channels. A divider is used to divide the received light into a plurality of light signals, which are combined with a local oscillator signal, which may possess different temporal phase across at the light signals, to provide a plurality of signals for detection by light detectors for processing into a spatial estimation of the remote environment.
column15: DIAZ FERNANDO
column32: See also references of EP 3994488A4

column12: Optical circulator
column13: Various forms of optical circulator are disclosed. The optical circulators act on polarisation of the light to direct light between its ports. Also disclosed are systems and methods for facilitating estimation of a spatial profile of an environment based on a light detection and ranging (LiDAR) based technique. The systems and method may include or use one or more of the various forms of optical circulator. In one arrangement, the present disclosure facilitates spatial profile estimation based on directing light over one dimension, such as along the vertical direction. In another arrangement, by further directing the one-dimensionally directed light in another dimension, such as along the horizontal direction, the present disclosure facilitates spatial profile estimation based on directing light in two dimensions.
column15: DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: 광 서큘레이터
column13: 다양한 형태의 광 서큘레이터들이 공개된다. 광 서큘레이터들은 빛의 편광 상에 작용하여 그 포트들 사이의 빛을 지향시킨다. 또한 공개되는 것은 빛 감지 및 범위 측정(LiDAR) 기반 기술에 기초한 환경에서 공간적 프로파일의 추정을 용이하게 하는 시스템 및 방법이다. 일 배치에서, 본 발명은 수직 방향을 따르는 것과 같은 1개 차원에 걸쳐 빛을 지향시키는 것에 기초하여 공간적 프로파일 추정을 용이하게 한다. 다른 배치에서, 1차원으로 지향된 빛을 수평 방향을 따르는 것과 같은 다른 차원으로 더 지향시킴으로써, 본 발명은 2개 차원에서 빛을 지향시키는 것에 기초하여 공간적 프로파일 추정을 용이하게 한다.
column15: DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: SISTEMAS DE VISION HIPERESTEREOSCOPICA.
column13: Sistema de visión hiperestereoscópica. El sistema es aplicable a microscopios, tales como microscopios quirúrgicos, lupas binoculares de trabajo e incluso gafas de porte personal, y consiste en modificar el distanciamiento entre los ejes ópticos (3 - 3"'') del microscopio (1) o del aparato de que se trate, aumentándolo en una magnitud del orden de tres veces superior, con el concurso de una pareja de superficies reflectantes (4 - 5) para cada eje óptico (3), de manera que se consigue un sustancial reforzamiento de la estereopsis de los objetos vistos a su través. Concretamente utiliza una superficie reflectante interna (4), dispuesta a 45º con respecto al respectivo eje óptico (3) del aparato, que provoca una inflexión de 90º, orientada hacia afuera, en la trayectoria del haz, mientras que una segunda superficie reflectante (5), situada por fuera de la primera y sensiblemente paralela a la misma, determina una nueva inflexión de 90º, contraria a la anterior y el pretendido desfase lateral externo de los rayos (6 - 6"'') procedentes del foco con respecto a los ejes ópticos (3 - 3"'') del aparato. Figura 1.
column15: DIAZ ESTEVEZ FERNANDO

column12: Self-contained depot for storage and delivery of fuel
column13: The self-contained fuel depot has a tank with a capacity of more than 3,000 litre coupled to an electrically driven (11) pump (10) to deliver the fuel. The fuel passes through a meter (12) as it is delivered. The tank is assembled with the ancillary components on a base (3) fitted with feet (2). When the depot is on the ground a wire fence is supported on posts set into the base plate. The base also collects any spillage. The depot has a heavy hook (20) at the top to allow lifting with a crane. The ancillary equipment is mounted on a post (8) which is placed in an enclosure at the edge of the depot, together with a cash handler (9).

column12: Dispositivo de protección telescópico para vástago de actuadores hidráulicos y neumáticos
column13: La presente invención se refiere a un dispositivo de protección telescópica del vástago, elemento que es esencial en la operación de un actuador neumático o hidráulico lineal, cuando está instalado en un equipo de construcción, tal como una retroexcavadora o un compactador de basura. El dispositivo está configurado de tal manera que se adapta a la geometría del actuador, durante su operación, protegiendo la integridad del vástago y de todos los elementos de sellamiento del actuador, generando una resistencia mecánica frente a impactos ocasionados por fuerzas externas.
column14: G & L IND DE SOLUCIONES S A S

column12: Predicting audience response for scripting
column13: Various technologies described herein pertain to automatic prediction of an anticipated audience response for scripting. A sub-document unit can be received, where the sub-document unit can be part of a script. The sub-document unit, for example, can be a sentence, a paragraph, a scene, or substantially any other portion of the script. Content of the sub-document unit and a context of the sub-document unit can be analyzed to extract features of the sub-document unit. A predictive model can be employed to predict an anticipated audience response to the sub-document unit based upon the features of the sub-document unit. Moreover, the anticipated audience response to the sub-document unit predicted by the predictive model can be output.

column12: SELF-PROPELLED VEHICLE FOR DRILLING ROCK FOR SMALL-SCALE UNDERGROUND MINING, MOUNTED ON WHEELS AND HAVING AN ARTICULATED CHASSIS
column13: In summary, the utility model according to the invention is applied to an original articulated drilling vehicle, which has two purposes. The first is to improve lateral stability of the vehicle when it turns, and the second is to have access to tunnels or galleries of restricted height, with the vehicle being very manoeuvrable and compact. The drilling vehicle carries out works to drill holes in underground mining. After having created the holes, the vehicle is removed from the area so that the mine personnel can place the dynamite and the blowing-up process is carried out in the area where dynamite was placed. Said activities can be for the purpose of extracting minerals or advancing the tunnel towards the mineral vein. The main characteristic of the invention is that is enables drilling works to be carried out in tunnels with narrow sections where, until now, self-propelled drilling vehicles could not enter. In these tunnels with narrow sections, the mineral extraction works are carried out artisanally or manually, and expose the personnel working on these operations to health risks.
column15: DIAZ LÓPEZ FERNANDO

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO DE PERSONALIZACION DE LA DUREZA, RESISTENCIA Y DURABILIDAD DE ESTRUCTURAS DE APOYO O ASIENTO Y ESTRUCTURA DE APOYO O ASIENTO ASI OBTENIDA.
column13: Procedimiento de personalización de la dureza, resistencia y durabilidad de estructuras de apoyo o asiento y estructura de apoyo o asiento así obtenida. Partiendo de estructura de apoyo, estructuradas en uno de sus componentes por medio de un substrato formado a base de al menos una capa (1) de material fibroso y al menos de una capa (2) de material soporte, unidas entre sí mediante fibras o mechas de fibras (3) emergentes de la capa fibrosa (1) y que penetran en la capa soporte (2), tales mechas (3) no sólo actúan como nexo de unión entre ambas capas sino que lo hacen paralelamente como medios de rigidización de la base, permitiendo que dicha rigidización sea variable en función de la longitud de que se dote a dichas mechas (3), así como de la densidad o número de mechas por unidad de superficie. De esta manera puede aumentarse la rigidez y la resistencia de la base de apoyo en aquellas zonas de la misma que vayan a verse sometidas a mayores esfuerzos. También puede mortificarse el grado de rigidez variando la dirección de las mechas (3), desde una posición perpendicular al plano general de la base a una posición inclinada. Figura 2.

column12: PREDICTING AUDIENCE RESPONSE FOR SCRIPTING
column13: Various technologies described herein pertain to automatic prediction of an anticipated audience response for scripting. A sub-document unit can be received, where the sub-document unit can be part of a script. The sub-document unit, for example, can be a sentence, a paragraph, a scene, or substantially any other portion of the script. Content of the sub-document unit and a context of the sub-document unit can be analyzed to extract features of the sub-document unit. A predictive model can be employed to predict an anticipated audience response to the sub-document unit based upon the features of the sub-document unit. Moreover, the anticipated audience response to the sub-document unit predicted by the predictive model can be output.
column15: DIAZ FERNANDO DAVID

column12: Process for customizing the hardness, resistance and durability of support or seating structures, and support or seating structure thus obtained
column13: Starting with support structures, constructed in one of the components thereof by means of a substrate formed from at least one layer 1 of fibrous material and at least one layer 2 of support material, which are joined together by means of fibres or fibres wicks 3 emerging from the fibrous layer 1 and which penetrate the support layer 2, said wicks 3 act not only as joining connection between both layers but do this in parallel like means for stiffening the base, allowing said stiffening to be variable as a function of the length given to said wicks 3, the density or number of wicks per unit of surface area also being variable. In this way, it is possible to increase the stiffness and the resistance of the support base in those areas of it which will be subjected to greater forces. It is also possible to modify the degree of rigidity by varying the direction of the wicks 3, from a position perpendicular to the general plane of the base to an inclined position.

column12: Vehículo electrohidráulico dual para desarrollo de túneles y fortificación de techos
column13: Un vehículo electrohidráulico dual para usarse en las etapas de desarrollo de túneles y en fortificación de techos de la minería subterránea. column12: Formulation for oral delivery of iron complexes - comprises water-soluble adduct comprising polyhydroxylated trivalent iron complex with soluble albumin
column13: Adducts of trivalent iron polyhydroxylate complexes with soluble albumin, method for obtaining them and pharmaceutical and dietetic preparations which contain them.The water-soluble adduct includes a trivalent iron polyhydroxylate complex with soluble desensitised albumen. The polyhydroxylate compound includes a compound which contains more than one hydroxyl group and which is able to form compounds with trivalent iron. The albumin is subjected to alkaline and oxidising expression treatment for solubility without affecting molecular weight. The adduct is obtained by mixing the ferric complex solution with the treated albumin solution. These adducts are suitable for the oral administration of ferric complexes, for which they can be used in treating iron deficiencies and/or supplements of said element.

column12: ADUCTOS DE COMPLEJOS POLIHIDROXILADOS DE HIERRO TRIVALENTE CON ALBUMINA SOLUBLE, METODO DE OBTENCION Y PREPARACIONES FARMACEUTICAS Y DIETETICAS QUE LOS CONTIENEN.
column13: Aductos de complejos polihidroxilados de hierro trivalente con albúmina soluble, método de obtención y preparaciones farmacéuticas y dietéticas que los contienen. El aducto, soluble en agua, comprende un complejo polihidroxilado de hierro trivalente con albúmina soluble y desensibilizada. El compuesto polihidroxilado comprende un compuesto que contiene más de un grupo hidroxilo y que es capaz de formar complejos con hierro trivalente. La albúmina ha sido sometida a un tratamiento término, alcalino y oxidante para su solubilización sin afectar a su peso molecular. El aducto se obtiene mezclando la solución del complejo férrico con la solución de albúmina tratada. Estos aductos son adecuados para la administración oral de complejos férricos, por lo que pueden utilizarse para el tratamiento de estados carenciales de hierro y/o para el aporte de dicho elemento.
column15: FUSSI FERNANDO;;DIAZ VICTOR

column12: CHEST/SEAT WITH DOUBLE TABLE
column13: The present invention relates to a chest/seat with a double table, which allows one to sit on it and to work on one or two service tables which can be disassembled and which is able to move by means of its wheels. The main characteristic feature is the body of this chest, which is formed by a tubular frame and which can incorporate various parts in its outer sides, leaving its central space for the storage of clothes or other articles, it being possible to use moreover the lid of this chest as a seat, being ergonomic and able to support loads of up to 160 kg. The first two extendable stations are pulled out and extended from the compartments of the outer side surfaces and the two tables are joined to them so that, once mounted, they can be worked on. A third extendable station is located on the rear side of the frame and has the function of a pulling device and a fourth extendable station is located in one of the corners and supports both a sunshade and a lectern which are both adjustable. Finally, a foldable platform can be incorporated in and fixed underneath this chest where required, so that it is also possible to store in it various articles inside its two compartments.

column12: MEJORAS INTRODUCIDAS EN CONJUNTOS BASE-COLCHON PARA CAMAS.
column13: Mejoras introducidas en conjuntos base-colchón para camas. Fundamentalmente consisten en recubrir al menos una de las caras mayores del colchón, la que ha de ser su cara operativo, opcionalmente ambas caras, con una lámina impermeable y transpirable, de manera que dicha lámina constituya una barrera a los líquidos, concretamente al sudor y a otros fluidos orgánicos, permitiendo sin embargo el paso del aire para mantener unas óptimas condiciones de aireación tanto para la piel del usuario como para el interior del colchón, lámina que se fija al colchón a través de la costura perimetral correspondiente al remate del mismo o por cualquier otro medio, con carácter fijo, con carácter rasgable o incluso con carácter recambiable. El núcleo del colchón debe ser también transpirable para colaborar con la lámina impermeable y transpirable citada, y la base de apoyo del colchón debe combinar una máxima superficie de apoyo para dicho colchón con una máxima posibilidad de aireación para el mismo.

column12: SYSTEM FOR DRILLING RADIAL BOREHOLES WHICH USES THE COINCIDENCE BETWEEN THE DRILLING SPINDLE AND THE ROTATION SHAFT AND IS MOUNTED ON A JUMBO FOR UNDERGROUND MINING
column13: The invention can be used in underground mining, being mounted on a device commonly known as a rock drilling jumbo. The system of the invention is used for systems for drilling long radial holes. In ore extraction in underground mining, long radial holes are usually drilled in a fan pattern to create the hole in which explosives for fragmenting the rock will be placed. It is important that each hole made has a maximum deviation of 1.5° to promote the fragmentation of the rock to be extracted. Mining equipment for drilling long radial boreholes currently exists, this type of borehole being routinely used in underground mining. In the mining market, this equipment is called a longhole jumbo drill. The most frequently used include the Simba S7D, the Tamrock Quasar, and the Raptor LH.
column15: DIAZ LOPEZ FERNANDO MISAEL

column12: AN OPTICAL BEAM DIRECTOR
column13: Spatial profiling systems and components for use in spatial profiling systems are described, as well as methods for spatial profiling. Various embodiments include a beam director and a bidirectional optical subsystem, for example an optical circulator, downstream of the beam director, in an outgoing light path. In some embodiments the beam director and bidirectional optical subsystem or optical circulator are integrated components, for example integrated onto a common substrate. Embodiments of dispersion components for an optical beam director are described that have an input slab and an array of waveguides optically coupled to the input slab. The input slab diffracts the outgoing light, like in an arrayed waveguide grating, and the array of waveguides have ends across the diffracted outgoing light. The dispersion components may further have or may lack an output slab.
column15: DIAZ FERNANDO;;PULIKKASERIL CIBBY

column12: FRONT END MOTOR-GENERATOR SYSTEM AND HYBRID ELECTRIC VEHICLE OPERATING METHOD
column13: A system and method are provided for hybrid electric internal combustion engine applications in which a motor-generator, a narrow switchable coupling and a torque transfer unit therebetween are arranged and positioned in the constrained environment at the front of an engine in applications such as commercial vehicles, off-road vehicles and stationary engine installations. The motor-generator is preferably positioned laterally offset from the switchable coupling, which is co-axially-arranged with the front end of the engine crankshaft. The switchable coupling is an integrated unit in which a crankshaft vibration damper, an engine accessory drive pulley and a disengageable clutch overlap such that the axial depth of the clutch-pulley-damper unit is nearly the same as a conventional belt drive pulley and engine damper. The front end motor-generator system includes an electrical energy store that receives electrical energy generated by the motor-generator when the coupling is engaged. When the coupling is disengaged, the motor-generator may drive the pulley portion of the clutch-pulley-damper to drive the engine accessories using energy returned from the energy store, independent of the engine crankshaft.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: VORDEREND-MOTOR/GENERATOR-SYSTEM UND HYBRIDELEKTROFAHRZEUGBETRIEBSVERFAHREN
column13: Es werden ein System und ein Verfahren für Hybridelektro-Brennkraftmaschinen-Anwendungen bereitgestellt, bei denen ein Motor/Generator, eine schmale schaltbare Kupplungsvorrichtung und eine Drehmomentübertragungseinheit dazwischen in der beschränkten Umgebung am vorderen Ende einer Kraftmaschine bei Anwendungen wie beispielsweise Nutzfahrzeugen, Geländefahrzeugen und stationären Kraftmaschinenanlagen angeordnet und positioniert sind. Der Motor/Generator ist vorzugsweise von der schaltbaren Kupplungsvorrichtung, die koaxial mit dem Vorderende der Kraftmaschinenkurbelwelle angeordnet ist, lateral versetzt positioniert. Die schaltbare Kupplungsvorrichtung ist eine integrierte Einheit, bei der sich ein Kurbelwellenschwingungsdämpfer, eine Kraftmaschinennebenaggregatantriebsriemenscheibe und eine ausrückbare Kupplung so überlappen, dass die axiale Tiefe der Kupplungs-Riemenscheiben-Dämpfer-Einheit nahezu einer/einem herkömmlichen Riemenantriebsscheibe und Kraftmaschinendämpfer entspricht. Das vorderendseitige Motor/Generator-System enthält einen elektrischen Energiespeicher, der durch den Motor/Generator erzeugte elektrische Energie empfängt, wenn die Kupplungsvorrichtung eingerückt ist. Wenn die Kupplungsvorrichtung ausgerückt ist, kann der Motor/Generator den Riemenscheibenteil des Kupplungs-Riemenscheiben-Dämpfers unabhängig von der Kraftmaschinenkurbelwelle dahingehend antreiben, die Kraftmaschinennebenaggregate unter Verwendung von vom Energiespeicher zurückgeführter Energie anzutreiben.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: Front End Motor-Generator System and Hybrid Electric Vehicle Operating Method
column13: A system and method are provided for hybrid electric internal combustion engine applications in which a motor-generator, a narrow switchable coupling and a torque transfer unit therebetween are arranged and positioned in the constrained environment at the front of an engine in applications such as commercial vehicles, off-road vehicles and stationary engine installations. The motor-generator is preferably positioned laterally offset from the switchable coupling, which is co-axially-arranged with the front end of the engine crankshaft. The switchable coupling is an integrated unit in which a crankshaft vibration damper, an engine accessory drive pulley and a disengageable clutch overlap such that the axial depth of the clutch-pulley-damper unit is nearly the same as a conventional belt drive pulley and engine damper. The front end motor-generator system includes an electrical energy store that receives electrical energy generated by the motor-generator when the coupling is engaged. When the coupling is disengaged, the motor-generator may drive the pulley portion of the clutch-pulley-damper to drive the engine accessories using energy returned from the energy store, independent of the engine crankshaft.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: VORDEREND-MOTOR/GENERATOR-SYSTEM UND HYBRIDELEKTROFAHRZEUGBETRIEBSVERFAHREN
column13: Es werden ein System und ein Verfahren für Hybridelektro-Brennkraftmaschinen-Anwendungen bereitgestellt, bei denen ein Motor/Generator, eine schmale schaltbare Kupplungsvorrichtung und eine Drehmomentübertragungseinheit dazwischen in der beschränkten Umgebung am vorderen Ende einer Kraftmaschine bei Anwendungen wie beispielsweise Nutzfahrzeugen, Geländefahrzeugen und stationären Kraftmaschinenanlagen angeordnet und positioniert sind. Der Motor/Generator ist vorzugsweise von der schaltbaren Kupplungsvorrichtung, die koaxial mit dem Vorderende der Kraftmaschinenkurbelwelle angeordnet ist, lateral versetzt positioniert. Die schaltbare Kupplungsvorrichtung ist eine integrierte Einheit, bei der sich ein Kurbelwellenschwingungsdämpfer, eine Kraftmaschinennebenaggregatantriebsriemenscheibe und eine ausrückbare Kupplung so überlappen, dass die axiale Tiefe der Kupplungs-Riemenscheiben-Dämpfer-Einheit nahezu einer/einem herkömmlichen Riemenantriebsscheibe und Kraftmaschinendämpfer entspricht. Das vorderendseitige Motor/Generator-System enthält einen elektrischen Energiespeicher, der durch den Motor/Generator erzeugte elektrische Energie empfängt, wenn die Kupplungsvorrichtung eingerückt ist. Wenn die Kupplungsvorrichtung ausgerückt ist, kann der Motor/Generator den Riemenscheibenteil des Kupplungs-Riemenscheiben-Dämpfers unabhängig von der Kraftmaschinenkurbelwelle dahingehend antreiben, die Kraftmaschinennebenaggregate unter Verwendung von vom Energiespeicher zurückgeführter Energie anzutreiben.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: FRONTMOTORGENERATORSYSTEM UND BETRIEBSVERFAHREN EINES HYBRIDELEKTROFAHRZEUGS
column13: Es werden ein System und Verfahren für Hybrid-Elektro-Verbrennungsmotoranwendungen bereitgestellt, wobei ein Motorgenerator, eine schmale schaltbare Kopplung und eine Drehmomentübertragungseinheit dazwischen angeordnet und in der beschränkten Umgebung an der Vorderseite eines Motors in Anwendungen, wie etwa Nutzfahrzeugen, Geländefahrzeugen und stationären Motorinstallationen, positioniert sind. Der Motorgenerator ist vorzugsweise seitlich versetzt von der schaltbaren Kopplung positioniert, die koaxial mit dem vorderen Ende der Motorkurbelwelle angeordnet ist. Die schaltbare Kopplung ist eine integrierte Einheit, in der sich ein Kurbelwellenschwingungsdämpfer, eine Antriebsriemenscheibe eines Motornebenaggregats und eine ausrückbare Kupplung überlappen, sodass die axiale Tiefe der Einheit aus Kupplung, Riemenscheibe und Dämpfer nahezu derjenigen bei einer bzw. einem herkömmlichen Riemenantriebsscheibe und Motordämpfer entspricht. Das Frontmotorgeneratorsystem am vorderen Ende schließt einen elektrischen Energiespeicher ein, der elektrische Energie aufnimmt, die von dem Motorgenerator erzeugt wird, wenn die Kopplung eingerückt ist. Wenn die Kopplung ausgerückt ist, kann der Motorgenerator den Riemenscheibenteil von Kupplung, Riemenscheibe und Dämpfer antreiben, um die Motornebenaggregate unter Verwendung von Energie, die von dem Energiespeicher zurückgegeben wird, unabhängig von der Motorkurbelwelle anzutreiben.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: Front end motor-generator system and hybrid electric vehicle operating method
column13: A system and method are provided for hybrid electric internal combustion engine applications in which a motor-generator, a narrow switchable coupling and a torque transfer unit therebetween are arranged and positioned in the constrained environment at the front of an engine in applications such as commercial vehicles, off-road vehicles and stationary engine installations. The motor-generator is preferably positioned laterally offset from the switchable coupling, which is co-axially-arranged with the front end of the engine crankshaft. The switchable coupling is an integrated unit in which a crankshaft vibration damper, an engine accessory drive pulley and a disengageable clutch overlap such that the axial depth of the clutch-pulley-damper unit is nearly the same as a conventional belt drive pulley and engine damper. The front end motor-generator system includes an electrical energy store that receives electrical energy generated by the motor-generator when the coupling is engaged. When the coupling is disengaged, the motor-generator may drive the pulley portion of the clutch-pulley-damper to drive the engine accessories using energy returned from the energy store, independent of the engine crankshaft.

column12: VORDEREND-MOTOR/GENERATOR-SYSTEM UND HYBRIDELEKTROFAHRZEUGBETRIEBSVERFAHREN
column13: Es werden ein System und ein Verfahren für Hybridelektro-Brennkraftmaschinen-Anwendungen bereitgestellt, bei denen ein Motor/Generator, eine schmale schaltbare Kupplungsvorrichtung und eine Drehmomentübertragungseinheit dazwischen in der beschränkten Umgebung am vorderen Ende einer Kraftmaschine bei Anwendungen wie beispielsweise Nutzfahrzeugen, Geländefahrzeugen und stationären Kraftmaschinenanlagen angeordnet und positioniert sind. Der Motor/Generator ist vorzugsweise von der schaltbaren Kupplungsvorrichtung, die koaxial mit dem Vorderende der Kraftmaschinenkurbelwelle angeordnet ist, lateral versetzt positioniert. Die schaltbare Kupplungsvorrichtung ist eine integrierte Einheit, bei der sich ein Kurbelwellenschwingungsdämpfer, eine Kraftmaschinennebenaggregatantriebsriemenscheibe und eine ausrückbare Kupplung so überlappen, dass die axiale Tiefe der Kupplungs-Riemenscheiben-Dämpfer-Einheit nahezu einer/einem herkömmlichen Riemenantriebsscheibe und Kraftmaschinendämpfer entspricht. Das vorderendseitige Motor/Generator-System enthält einen elektrischen Energiespeicher, der durch den Motor/Generator erzeugte elektrische Energie empfängt, wenn die Kupplungsvorrichtung eingerückt ist. Wenn die Kupplungsvorrichtung ausgerückt ist, kann der Motor/Generator den Riemenscheibenteil des Kupplungs-Riemenscheiben-Dämpfers unabhängig von der Kraftmaschinenkurbelwelle dahingehend antreiben, die Kraftmaschinennebenaggregate unter Verwendung von vom Energiespeicher zurückgeführter Energie anzutreiben.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: Airflow Plate Fins
column13: Curved airflow plate fins deployed upon rockets to guide the trajectory under the action of given forces. The fins are comprise relatively high gauge metal. They are located on the rocket in a triangular arrangement. When deployed. the fins contribute to deceleration and breaking. The airflow plates can be extended outwardly from their housing, and then rotated transversely with respect to the longitudinal axis of the rocket. The airflow plate fins have geometric openings to improve their performance against incoming forces given that under supersonic speed. Their curved shape increases the capabilities of friction between the forces acting against them.
column15: GOMEZ DE AVILA DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: WIRELESS INTELLIGENT DEVICE FOR PERFORMING FINANCIAL OPERATIONS OFFLINE, WHICH HAS ITS OWN POWER SUPPLY, SAFETY AND AUTHENTICATION.
column13: Intelligent device with a System and Method, with a Processing unit, inner storage, keyboard, screen, biometric reader, radio frequency signal transmitter, its own power supply, which may be presented in two forms, but not limited thereto: 1) as a Smart Card, with standard measures 85mm x 54mm x 0.8mm and further characteristics defined in ISO 7810 and made of different types of plastic such as PVC (Polyvinyl Chloride) and ABS (Acrylonitrile Butadiene Styrene); or 2) as a Special Device, with measures and characteristics suitable for different uses and needs (heavy duty, extreme weathers, people with disabilities, illiterates, etc). It allows the information to be exchanged between: users and users; users and businesses, as well as users and financial institutions, typically in the form of financial transactions, however it is not limited thereto, a central server connection or a telecommunication network connection being not required, so that it may work in an independent manner, the invention may establish a communication between smart card-smart card, smart card-Special device, Special device-Special device and with other devices, for example: Point of sale terminals, ATM´s, Smart phones, tablets, pc’s, which support the standard communication and safety protocol (i.e.: NFC), the smart card form is for, optionally, being compatible with the thousands of ATM and POS devices, which use the standard EMV chip, defined by the EMVCo (Europay, Mastercard and Visa Consortium), the Special Device form being used for providing a device for special needs and with a higher resistance to heavy duty conditions, changing and extreme temperatures, flexibility, people with disabilities and independence.

column12: VORDEREND-MOTOR/GENERATOR-SYSTEM UND HYBRIDELEKTROFAHRZEUGBETRIEBSVERFAHREN
column13: Es werden ein System und ein Verfahren für Hybridelektro-Brennkraftmaschinen-Anwendungen bereitgestellt, bei denen ein Motor/Generator, eine schmale schaltbare Kupplungsvorrichtung und eine Drehmomentübertragungseinheit dazwischen in der beschränkten Umgebung am vorderen Ende einer Kraftmaschine bei Anwendungen wie beispielsweise Nutzfahrzeugen, Geländefahrzeugen und stationären Kraftmaschinenanlagen angeordnet und positioniert sind. Der Motor/Generator ist vorzugsweise von der schaltbaren Kupplungsvorrichtung, die koaxial mit dem Vorderende der Kraftmaschinenkurbelwelle angeordnet ist, lateral versetzt positioniert. Die schaltbare Kupplungsvorrichtung ist eine integrierte Einheit, bei der sich ein Kurbelwellenschwingungsdämpfer, eine Kraftmaschinennebenaggregatantriebsriemenscheibe und eine ausrückbare Kupplung so überlappen, dass die axiale Tiefe der Kupplungs-Riemenscheiben-Dämpfer-Einheit nahezu einer/einem herkömmlichen Riemenantriebsscheibe und Kraftmaschinendämpfer entspricht. Das vorderendseitige Motor/Generator-System enthält einen elektrischen Energiespeicher, der durch den Motor/Generator erzeugte elektrische Energie empfängt, wenn die Kupplungsvorrichtung eingerückt ist. Wenn die Kupplungsvorrichtung ausgerückt ist, kann der Motor/Generator den Riemenscheibenteil des Kupplungs-Riemenscheiben-Dämpfers unabhängig von der Kraftmaschinenkurbelwelle dahingehend antreiben, die Kraftmaschinennebenaggregate unter Verwendung von vom Energiespeicher zurückgeführter Energie anzutreiben.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: REFRIGERATION DEVICE
column13: The invention relates to a refrigeration device comprising heat-insulating components, such as a heat-insulating housing (10), with a heat insulation layer (14) which is produced by foaming between an inner lining and an outer lining. A receiving pocket (20) for introducing components projects into the heat insulation layer, has an opening side for introducing the components and rests in a cut-out section of the inner and outer lining. On its opening side, the receiving pocket has an edge (26) which extends around its outer contour and which is oriented away from its receiving area. Said edge (26) is provided with elements which, when the receiving pocket is in its final position, rest elastically against the edge areas of the cut-out section of the receiving pocket, outside the heat insulation layer, and seal the receiving pocket in relation to the cut-out section.

column12: Front End Motor-Generator System and Hybrid Electric Vehicle Operating Method
column13: A system and method are provided for hybrid electric internal combustion engine applications in which a motor-generator, a narrow switchable coupling and a torque transfer unit therebetween are arranged and positioned in the constrained environment at the front of an engine in applications such as commercial vehicles, off-road vehicles and stationary engine installations. The motor-generator is preferably positioned laterally offset from the switchable coupling, which is co-axially-arranged with the front end of the engine crankshaft. The switchable coupling is an integrated unit in which a crankshaft vibration damper, an engine accessory drive pulley and a disengageable clutch overlap such that the axial depth of the clutch-pulley-damper unit is nearly the same as a conventional belt drive pulley and engine damper. The front end motor-generator system includes an electrical energy store that receives electrical energy generated by the motor-generator when the coupling is engaged. When the coupling is disengaged, the motor-generator may drive the pulley portion of the clutch-pulley-damper to drive the engine accessories using energy returned from the energy store, independent of the engine crankshaft.

column12: LENKPAUSEN-VORBEREITUNGSSYSTEM FÜR EIN HYBRIDFAHRZEUG
column13: Ein Hybridelektrofahrzeug-Steuersystem und -verfahren initiieren Steuerstrategien für aktives Laden und Leistungsrationieren gemäß dem Bestimmen, dass ein vorhergesagter Ladezustand einer Elektroenergie-Speichereinheit während einer antizipierten Nichtlenkzeit unter einem antizipierten Energieverbrauch während der antizipierten Nichtlenkzeit liegt. Die Bestimmung wird vor der Nichtlenkzeit vorgenommen und das aktive Laden und Rationieren werden vor der Nichtlenkzeit initiiert, um sicherzustellen, dass ein Ladezustand der Elektroenergie-Speichereinheit ausreichend ist, um den antizipierten Energieverbrauch während der Nichtlenkzeit bereitzustellen.

column12: SISTEMA DE MEDICION DE CAUDAL DE TIPO LAMINAR.
column13: Sistema de medición de caudal de tipo laminar. El aparato está pensado para medir el caudal de fluidos, líquidos o gases, que circulen por conductos. Para un fluido determinado, el caudal es calculado por el propio aparato a partir de los datos geométricos del mismo y de diversas magnitudes físicas que mide. El núcleo del dispositivo está formado por una pluralidad de conductos iguales dispuestos en paralelo (1), de forma que el fluido entra por (5) y se divide en tantas partes como conductos, atravesándolos hasta la salida (6). Todos o algunos de estos conductos tienen orificios en sus paredes (2) que los comunican con tres cámaras independientes (3). El aparato incorpora unos transductores de presión y temperatura conectados a un circuito electrónico con el que calcula, en tiempo real, el caudal a partir de la medida de las diferencias de presión entre los racores (4) conectados a estas cámaras.
column15: LOPEZ PENA FERNANDO;;DEIBE DIAZ ALVARO

column12: BLOCKCHAIN-BASED LICENSE MANAGEMENT FRAMEWORK
column13: Systems and methods are described for license management. A system for license management includes a smart contract (158, 458) configured to record a licensing agreement between a first party (140) and a second party (150) on usage of a network function (166 1-N , 306A-306C, 416A-416C). The smart contract (158) is persisted in a trade blockchain (128). The system also includes an e-licensing manager agent (200A-200C). The e-licensing manager agent (162 1-N , 200, 200A-200C) is configured to retrieve the licensing agreement from the smart contract (158). The e-licensing manager agent (162 1-N , 200, 200A-200C) is configured to monitor a usage of the network function (166 1-N , 306A-306C, 416A-416C) by the second party (150) in real-time based on the licensing agreement, record actions of the usage of the network function (166 1-N , 306A-306C, 416A-416C), and create a transaction record based on the recorded actions in an operation blockchain (130).

column12: Driver break preparation system for hybrid vehicle
column13: A hybrid electric vehicle control system and process initiates active charging and power rationing control strategies in accordance with determining that a predicted state of charge of an electrical energy storage unit during an anticipated period of non-driving will be below an anticipated energy consumption during the anticipated period of non-driving. The determination is made, and the active charging and rationing are initiated, in advance of the period of non-driving in order to ensure that a state of charge of the electrical energy storage unit is sufficient to supply the anticipated energy consumption during the period of non-driving.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID D;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: Front end motor-generator system and hybrid electric vehicle operating method
column13: A system and method are provided for hybrid electric internal combustion engine applications in which a motor-generator, a narrow switchable coupling and a torque transfer unit therebetween are arranged and positioned in the constrained environment at the front of an engine in applications such as commercial vehicles, off-road vehicles and stationary engine installations. The motor-generator is preferably positioned laterally offset from the switchable coupling, which is co-axially-arranged with the front end of the engine crankshaft. The switchable coupling is an integrated unit in which a crankshaft vibration damper, an engine accessory drive pulley and a disengageable clutch overlap such that the axial depth of the clutch-pulley-damper unit is nearly the same as a conventional belt drive pulley and engine damper. The front end motor-generator system includes an electrical energy store that receives electrical energy generated by the motor-generator when the coupling is engaged. When the coupling is disengaged, the motor-generator may drive the pulley portion of the clutch-pulley-damper to drive the engine accessories using energy returned from the energy store, independent of the engine crankshaft.
column15: COLAVINCENZO DAVID D;;VENEGAS DIAZ FERNANDO

column12: Laminar-type volume measuring system, for measuring fluid volume, has pressure and temperature transducers connected to electronic circuit which calculates fluid volume in real time based on pressure difference between conduits
column13: Laminar-type volume measuring system has an electronic circuit for calculating fluid volume using measured geometric data and diverse physical magnitudes of fluid flowing through parallel conduits. Pressure and temperature transducers are connected to the electronic circuit which calculates fluid volume in real time based on the pressure difference between conduits. The conduits have orifices at the walls for connection to three independent chambers.

column12: Process for personalising the hardness, resistance and durability of supporting or seating structures, a supporting or seating structure obtained and a machine for obtaining the same
column13: Starting from supporting structures, one of their components is structured by means of a substrate formed on the basis of at least a layer (1) of fibrous material and at least a layer (2) of supporting material, joined to one another by means of fibres or fibre strands (3) projecting from the fibrous layer (1) and penetrating the supporting layer (2), said strands (3) not only serving as a means for joining both layers but being at the same time useful as means for stiffening the base, allowing such stiffening to be variable depending upon the length with which said strands (3) are provided, and the density or number of strands per surface unit. The stiffness and resistance of the supporting base can thus be increased in areas thereof that are to withstand greater strains. The extent of stiffness can also be modified by varying the direction of the strands (3) from a position at a right angle to the general plane of the base to an inclined position. This supporting structure or base, especially applicable for mattresses, is obtained by means of a machine having a number of needles (9) which produce fibrous strands from the fibrous layer of the supporting structure or base and insert the same in the supporting layer thereof, forming independent groups, being especially particular in that both the number of needles that are operative and the extent of penetration of said needles may be varied in each of the supporting structure or base to have strengthened areas of greater hardness, resistance and durability defined in such regions as are expected to withstand greater strains in their normal and subsequent use.

column12: MAQUINA PARA LA OBTENCION DE BASES DE APOYO PARA COLCHONERIA.

column12: Device and method for measuring ocular aberrations based on a curvature sensor (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: Device and method for the measurement of ocular aberrations based on a curvature sensor. Curvature sensor applied to the eye to determine ocular aberrations. The instrument uses as a nucleus a double-step ophthalmoscopic system that allows to record on a ccd camera consecutively or simultaneously two images in planes slightly displaced with respect to the pupillary plane. From these two images, an image corresponding to the contrast between both is obtained as the difference of intensities divided by the sum of the intensities point to point. From this contrast image, the wave aberration function is calculated. (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)

column12: ELECTROLYTIC STRIPPING
column13: The present invention is directed towards an electrochemical process for stripping corrosion and oxide products and oxidation resistant metallic coatings from a superalloy test sample. The process involves connecting the test sample to a lead of a power supply and submerging a portion of the test sample into a bath of electrolytic stripping solution with a pH less than 1. The test sample is then subjected to combined cycles of anodic and cathodic polarisation steps for a period of time which is effective to strip the corrosion and the oxide products and oxidation resistant metallic coatings from the test sample. The open circuit potential is measured before and after at least one step of the combined cycle of polarisation in order to monitor the progress of the coating removal, and, the test sample is removed from the electrolytic stripping solution when the corrosion and oxide products and oxidation resistant metallic coatings are removed and the open circuit potential is close to that of the original superalloy test sample (or the current value is getting closer to the passivation current value of the base material). The test sample lastly undergoes a final cleaning and rinsing step.

column12: Method of cutting sheet material.
column13: In accordance with the invention a method in wich N.C. machine is provided to cut sheet material like cloth paper, cardboard. plastic. plywood, wood and similar chelt materials with a thickness of up to 15 mm. The raw material can be available in the roll form or in laminate planar form. To feed material from the roll to the cutting area a motorized support is provided, in the way to prevent the material from stretching or being distorted before being cut in the table. In order to have maximum througput from the machine, the cutting table is a conveyor made of an .air and gas permeable material, and divided in three areas; feeding, cutting and removing area. Means are provided for the conveyor to prevent it to move during cutting time and to be moved by the X arm without changing the position to each other during feeding operation. In each of the cutting and removing areas is an X-Y computer controlled assembly. In the cutting area a plasma jet cutter managed by the X-Y assembly in that way that is posible for the cutting beam to reach every point of the surface. The power suply and the tank for the gas to be transformed in plasma are in a stationary position and the beam path is conveniently protected. The lower side of the feeding and cutting area is covered by a cage from wich air is continuously removed in order to prevent motion of the material to be cut and in order to remove smoke and ofher products that result from the cutting process. Another motive for this cage is to provide means to disipate the energy of the plasma jet beam. In the removing area is placed another X-Y computer controlled assembly with a head provided with a labelling and a suction device in order to automatically label and pick-up the cut parts and bring them to a storage area. Since normally the minimum length of the marker necesary to make a complete suit is about 5 to 7 m., and, due to the simultaneity of the cutting and removing operation the lenght of the two areas must be the same, a machine to be able to cut the entire marker at once would result extremely long. To avoid the problem, the sistem we are dealing with is provided with a control to cut the marker by sections, normally named "windows" but, and this is very important, "variable windows" in order to cut the patterns falling completely into the cutting area. That is why here, is enough to have the length of the window a little bit bigger that the biggest part to be cut.

column12: Front end motor-generator system and modular generator drive apparatus
column13: A system and method are provided for hybrid electric internal combustion engine applications in which a motor-generator, a narrow switchable coupling and a torque transfer unit therebetween are arranged and positioned in the constrained environment at the front of an engine in applications such as commercial vehicles, off-road vehicles and stationary engine installations. The motor-generator is preferably positioned laterally offset from the switchable coupling, which is co-axially-arranged with the front end of the engine crankshaft. The switchable coupling is an integrated unit in which a crankshaft vibration damper, an engine accessory drive pulley and a disengageable clutch overlap such that the axial depth of the clutch-pulley-damper unit is nearly the same as a conventional belt drive pulley and engine damper. The front end motor-generator system includes an electrical energy store that receives electrical energy generated by the motor-generator when the coupling is engaged. When the coupling is disengaged, the motor-generator may drive the pulley portion of the clutch-pulley-damper to drive the engine accessories using energy returned from the energy store, independent of the engine crankshaft.

column12: METHOD FOR ADJUSTING A BRAKE PEDAL CHARACTERISTIC
column13: A method is disclosed for adjusting a brake pedal characteristic (1) of a vehicle, wherein the vehicle comprises a brake pedal configured to generate a brake pedal deceleration demand and at least one further deceleration demand generating device to generate at least one further deceleration demand, wherein the vehicle is configured to decelerate according to the brake pedal deceleration demand and to the at least one further deceleration demand, wherein the method comprises the steps: step S1: determining an achievable deceleration potential (4) as a result of the further deceleration demand; step S2: generating a deceleration demand for adjusting the brake pedal deceleration demand at 0% brake pedal input according to the achievable deceleration potential; and step S3: adjusting the brake pedal characteristic (1, 3) of the vehicle in accordance with the deceleration demand generated in step S2. Further, a device, a vehicle, a computer program product and a storage medium are disclosed.

column12: COMPOSITION FOR THE DETECTION OF POSTPRANDIAL HYPERTRIGLYCERIDEMIA
column13: The invention relates to a composition of fatty acids, which can be used to detect moderate or severe postprandial hypertriglyceridemia in an individual and to determine an individual's capacity for metabolising postprandial triglycerides. The invention also relates to the method for obtaining data that can be used to detect moderate or severe postprandial hypertriglyceridemia in an individual and to the method for obtaining data that can be used to determine an individual's capacity for metabolising postprandial triglycerides, in which methods an individual's triglyceride level is determined at different times following the administration of the composition of the invention. Said methods can be used to identify individuals at risk of developing diseases such as metabolic syndrome, cardiovascular diseases, insulin resistance, atherosclerosis, etc., pathologies which are all associated with postprandial hypertriglyceridemia and a reduced capacity to metabolise fats.

column12: ITQ-25, new crystalline microporous material
column13: ITQ-25 (INSTITUTO DE TECNOLOGÍA QUÍMICA number 25) is a new crystalline microporous material with a framework of tetrahedral atoms connected by atoms capable of bridging the tetrahedral atoms, the tetrahedral atom framework being defined by the interconnections between the tetrahedrally coordinated atoms in its framework. ITQ-25 can be prepared in silicate compositions with a organic structure directing agent. It has a unique X-ray diffraction pattern, which identifies it as a new material. ITQ-25 is stable to calcination in air, absorbs hydrocarbons, and is catalytically active for hydrocarbon conversion.

column12: REFRIGERADOR, COMO FRIGORIFICO O CONGELADOR.
column13: The refrigerator includes a casing determined by a wall with an internal covering (4), an external covering (3) and an intervening heat-insulating layer (2), through which wall is fed, via a penetration duct, a breather tube from the refrigerator storage space to the outside. The penetration duct has a first section (5) followed by a second section (7) separated by means of an intervening wall (6 or 6') which can be perforated or even removed. The first section (5) has a surrounding lip (11) which fits externally over the external insulation (3), while the second section (7), shaped internally as a truncated cone (8), is pressure-fitted onto a formation (9) of the internal covering (4), said formation (9) being provided with a seal (10) which can also be perforated or removed. The penetration duct is prepared to prevent the injection of the foam that is to constitute the heat-insulating layer (2), from reaching the outside or from penetrating into the refrigeration compartment of the corresponding refrigerator. <IMAGE>

column12: Front End Motor-Generator System and Modular Generator Drive Apparatus
column13: A system and method are provided for hybrid electric internal combustion engine applications in which a motor-generator, a narrow switchable coupling and a torque transfer unit therebetween are arranged and positioned in the constrained environment at the front of an engine in applications such as commercial vehicles, off-road vehicles and stationary engine installations. The motor-generator is preferably positioned laterally offset from the switchable coupling, which is co-axially-arranged with the front end of the engine crankshaft. The switchable coupling is an integrated unit in which a crankshaft vibration damper, an engine accessory drive pulley and a disengageable clutch overlap such that the axial depth of the clutch-pulley-damper unit is nearly the same as a conventional belt drive pulley and engine damper. The front end motor-generator system includes an electrical energy store that receives electrical energy generated by the motor-generator when the coupling is engaged. When the coupling is disengaged, the motor-generator may drive the pulley portion of the clutch-pulley-damper to drive the engine accessories using energy returned from the energy store, independent of the engine crankshaft.

column12: SYSTEM FOR DETERMINING AND OPTIMIZING FOR RELEVANCE IN MATCH-MAKING SYSTEMS
column13: Disclosed are methods and apparatus for automatically determining the relevance of matches between entities. A set of one or more indicators of relevance for each of a plurality of matches may be detected, where each of the plurality of matches exists between a first entity and a different one of a plurality of entities. Each set of one or more indicators of relevance indicates a degree of two-way interest for a corresponding one of the plurality of matches, the degree of two-way interest indicating both a degree of interest of the first entity in the corresponding one of the plurality of entities and a degree of interest of the corresponding one of the plurality of entities in the first entity. A probability of relevance of each of the plurality of matches may be determined based at least in part upon a corresponding set of one or more indicators of relevance. Each of the plurality of matches may be ranked based at least in part on the corresponding probability of relevance. A ranking function may be trained based upon the probability of relevance of each of the plurality of matches. The ranking function may subsequently be applied to identify and rank matches (e.g., in the absence of indicators of relevance).

column12: Perimeter liquid-cooled electric machine and integrated power inverter
column13: A perimeter electric machine cooling arrangement includes a cooling conduit arranged to remove heat from an integrated housing containing an electric motor and a power inverter. The electrical connections between the electric motor and the power inverter are provided by flexible, pre-formed busbars that are arranged in pass over liquid cooling connections in the region between the electric motor and the power inverter. The integrated housing includes an intermediate cover over the electric motor and the power inverter portions of the housing, with a window through which the busbars can pass to reach the electric motor. The housing is further provided with an outer housing cover and seals that isolate the electric motor and the power inverter from the exterior environment and one another.

column12: Prefetching using dynamic user model to reduce latency
column13: A device includes a memory that stores a prefetching model. A control module receives a content page including one or more links each associated with selectable content and collects data associated with the content page. The collected data includes at least one of first data indicative of respective relationships between each of the links and a viewport of the device and second data indicative of characteristics of the viewport. The control module further assigns, using the prefetching model, respective scores to each of the links based on the collected data, and selectively generates, based on the assigned scores, a request to prefetch the selectable content associated with at least one of the links.

column12: PREFETCHING USING DYNAMIC USER MODEL TO REDUCE LATENCY
column13: A device includes a memory that stores a prefetching model. A control module receives a content page including one or more links each associated with selectable content and collects data associated with the content page. The collected data includes at least one of first data indicative of respective relationships between each of the links and a viewport of the device and second data indicative ofcharacteristics of the viewport. The control module further assigns, using the prefetching model, respective scores to each of the links based on the collected data, and selectively generates, based on the assigned scores, a request to prefetch the selectable content associated with at least one of the links.

column12: ITQ-25, NEW CRYSTALLINE MICROPOROUS MATERIAL
column13: ITQ-25 (INSTITUTO DE TECNOLOG↕A QU↕MICA number 25) is a new crystalline microporous material with a framework of tetrahedral atoms connected by atoms capable of bridging the tetrahedral atoms, the tetrahedral atom framework being defined by the interconnections between the tetrahedrally coordinated atoms in its framework. ITQ-25 can be prepared in silicate compositions with a organic structure directing agent. It has a unique X-ray diffraction pattern, which identifies it as a new material. ITQ-25 is stable to calcination in air, absorbs hydrocarbons, and is catalytically active for hydrocarbon conversion.

column12: VERFAHREN ZUM SCHNEIDEN VON FLACHMATERIAL.
column13: In accordance with the invention a method in wich N.C. machine is provided to cut sheet material like cloth, paper, cardboard, plastic, plywood, wood and similar chelt materials with a thickness of up to 15 mm. The raw material can be available in the roll form or in laminate planar form. <??>To feed material from the roll to the cutting area a motorized support is provided, in the way to prevent the material from stretching or being distorted before being cut in the table. <??>In order to have maximum througput from the machine, the cutting table is a conveyor made of an air and gas permeable material, and divided in three areas; feeding, cutting and removing area. Means are provided for the conveyor to prevent it to move during cutting time and to be moved by the X arm without changing the position to each other during feeding operation. <??>In each of the cutting and removing areas is an X-Y computer controlled assembly. In the cutting area a plasma jet cutter managed by the X-Y assembly in that way that is posible for the cutting beam to reach every point of the surface. The power suply and the tank for the gas to be transformed in plasma are in a stationary position and the beam path is conveniently protected. The lower side of the feeding and cutting area is covered by a cage from wich air is continuously removed in order to prevent motion of the material to be cut and in order to remove smoke and ofher products that result from the cutting process. Another motive for this cage is to provide means to disipate the energy of the plasma jet beam. <??>In the removing area is placed another X-Y computer controlled assembly with a head provided with a labelling and a suction device in order to automatically label and pick-up the cut parts and bring them to a storage area. <??>Since normally the minimum length of the marker necesary to make a complete suit is about 5 to 7 m., and, due to the simultaneity of the cutting and removing operation the lenght of the two areas must be the same, a machine to be able to cut the entire marker at once would result extremely long. To avoid the problem, the sistem we are dealing with is provided with a control to cut the marker by sections, normally named "windows" but, and this is very important, "variable windows" in order to cut the patterns falling completely into the cutting area. That is why here, is enough to have the length of the window a little bit bigger that the biggest part to be cut.

column12: SYSTEM FOR DETERMINING AND OPTIMIZING FOR RELEVANCE IN MATCH-MAKING SYSTEMS
column13: Disclosed are methods and apparatus for automatically determining the relevance of matches between entities. A set of one or more indicators of relevance for each of a plurality of matches may be detected, where each of the plurality of matches exists between a first entity and a different one of a plurality of entities. Each set of one or more indicators of relevance indicates a degree of two-way interest for a corresponding one of the plurality of matches, the degree of two-way interest indicating both a degree of interest of the first entity in the corresponding one of the plurality of entities and a degree of interest of the corresponding one of the plurality of entities in the first entity. A probability of relevance of each of the plurality of matches may be determined based at least in part upon a corresponding set of one or more indicators of relevance. Each of the plurality of matches may be ranked based at least in part on the corresponding probability of relevance. A ranking function may be trained based upon the probability of relevance of each of the plurality of matches. The ranking function may subsequently be applied to identify and rank matches (e.g., in the absence of indicators of relevance).

column12: PERIMETER LIQUID-COOLED ELECTRIC MACHINE AND INTEGRATED POWER INVERTER
column13: A perimeter electric machine cooling arrangement includes a cooling conduit arranged to remove heat from an integrated housing containing an electric motor and a power inverter. The electrical connections between the electric motor and the power inverter are provided by flexible, pre-formed busbars that are arranged in pass over liquid cooling connections in the region between the electric motor and the power inverter. The integrated housing includes an intermediate cover over the electric motor and the power inverter portions of the housing, with a window through which the busbars can pass to reach the electric motor. The housing is further provided with an outer housing cover and seals that isolate the electric motor and the power inverter from the exterior environment and one another.

column12: Refrigerator, such as fridge or freezer
column13: The refrigerator includes a casing determined by a wall with an internal covering (4), an external covering (3) and an intervening heat-insulating layer (2), through which wall is fed, via a penetration duct, a breather tube from the refrigerator storage space to the outside. The penetration duct has a first section (5) followed by a second section (7) separated by means of an intervening wall (6 or 6') which can be perforated or even removed. The first section (5) has a surrounding lip (11) which fits externally over the external insulation (3), while the second section (7), shaped internally as a truncated cone (8), is pressure-fitted onto a formation (9) of the internal covering (4), said formation (9) being provided with a seal (10) which can also be perforated or removed. column12: PROCEDIMIENTO PARA EFECTUAR LA INVERSION DE FLORA NO DESEADA QUE ES PERJUDICIAL PARA ELEMENTOS DE INSTALACIONES INDUSTRIALES QUE SE ENCUENTRAN SOBRE O POR DEBAJO DEL TERRENO.
column13: Procedimiento para efectuar la inversión de flora no deseada que es perjudicial para elementos de instalaciones industriales que se encuentran sobre o debajo del terreno; preferentemente, torres de transporte de energía eléctrica y/o telefonía o conducciones de transporte y/o de distribución de agua, productos químicos o de hidrocarburos y sus derivados. El procedimiento comprende: cortar la flora no deseada en una zona de servidumbre en la que se encuentran los elementos a proteger. La zona cortada queda libre para recibir la aplicación de productos fitosanitarios líquidos que impregnan la superficie cortada y evitan la nascencia de la flora no deseada. Con la aplicación de dicho líquido se controla el rebrote consiguiendo la eliminación de las raíces que afectan negativamente a las cimentaciones y a las conducciones que van por el subsuelo.

column12: LOCKING PIECE ASSEMBLY FOR LATCH BOLTS
column13: A locking piece assembly adapted for installation in a cylindrical lock and meant to engage a locking mechanism comprises a locking piece and a lock button. The locking piece has one end adapted to engage the locking mechanism and an opposite end with a connecting hook. The lock button has an aperture adapted for attachment to the locking piece connecting hook, and can be depressed to move the locking piece inward to engage the locking mechanism after the locking piece assembly is installed in the cylindrical lock. The lock button can be installed onto the locking piece by hand, specifically by inserting the connecting hook into the aperture on the lock button, pivoting the lock button with respect to the locking piece, and placing the locking piece and lock button into alignment. After installation, the connecting hook is held in place to prevent separation from the lock button aperture.

column12: Refrigerator, such as fridge or freezer
column13: The refrigerator includes a casing determined by a wall with an internal covering (4), an external covering (3) and an intervening heat-insulating layer (2), through which wall is fed, via a penetration duct, a breather tube from the refrigerator storage space to the outside. The penetration duct has a first section (5) followed by a second section (7) separated by means of an intervening wall (6 or 6') which can be perforated or even removed. The first section (5) has a surrounding lip (11) which fits externally over the external insulation (3), while the second section (7), shaped internally as a truncated cone (8), is pressure-fitted onto a formation (9) of the internal covering (4), said formation (9) being provided with a seal (10) which can also be perforated or removed. The penetration duct is prepared to prevent the injection of the foam that is to constitute the heat-insulating layer (2), from reaching the outside or from penetrating into the refrigeration compartment of the corresponding refrigerator.
column15: DIAZ LANDIBAR FERNANDO;;MELERO ARMENDARIZ JOSE RAMON

column12: System for determining and optimizing for relevance in match-making systems
column13: Disclosed are methods and apparatus for automatically determining the relevance of matches between entities. A set of one or more indicators of relevance for each of a plurality of matches may be detected, where each of the plurality of matches exists between a first entity and a different one of a plurality of entities. Each set of one or more indicators of relevance indicates a degree of two-way interest for a corresponding one of the plurality of matches, the degree of two-way interest indicating both a degree of interest of the first entity in the corresponding one of the plurality of entities and a degree of interest of the corresponding one of the plurality of entities in the first entity. A probability of relevance of each of the plurality of matches may be determined based at least in part upon a corresponding set of one or more indicators of relevance. Each of the plurality of matches may be ranked based at least in part on the corresponding probability of relevance. A ranking function may be trained based upon the probability of relevance of each of the plurality of matches. The ranking function may subsequently be applied to identify and rank matches (e.g., in the absence of indicators of relevance).

column12: PREFETCHING USING DYNAMIC USER MODEL TO REDUCE LATENCY
column13: A device includes a memory that stores a prefetching model. A control module receives a content page including one or more links each associated with selectable content and collects data associated with the content page. The collected data includes at least one of first data indicative of respective relationships between each of the links and a viewport of the device and second data indicative of characteristics of the viewport. The control module further assigns, using the prefetching model, respective scores to each of the links based on the collected data, and selectively generates, based on the assigned scores, a request to prefetch the selectable content associated with at least one of the links.

column12: FRONT END MOTOR-GENERATOR SYSTEM AND MODULAR GENERATOR DRIVE APPARATUS.
column13: A system and method are provided for hybrid electric internal combustion engine applications in which a motor-generator, a narrow switchable coupling and a torque transfer unit therebetween are arranged and positioned in the constrained environment at the front of an engine in applications such as commercial vehicles, off-road vehicles and stationary engine installations. The motor-generator is preferably positioned laterally offset from the switchable coupling, which is co-axially-arranged with the front end of the engine crankshaft. The switchable coupling is an integrated unit in which a crankshaft vibration damper, an engine accessory drive pulley and a disengageable clutch overlap such that the axial depth of the clutch-pulley-damper unit is nearly the same as a conventional belt drive pulley and engine damper. The front end motor-generator system includes an electrical energy store that receives electrical energy generated by the motor-generator when the coupling is engaged. Whe n the coupling is disengaged, the motor-generator may drive the pulley portion of the clutch-pulley-damper to drive the engine accessories using energy returned from the energy store, independent of the engine crankshaft.

column12: System and method of geo-based prediction in search result selection
column13: A system and method is disclosed for determining a prediction measurement, or measure, using geo-spatial information which can be used to determine whether or not to include type of information in search results. The prediction measurement comprises a measure of the likelihood that an item of the type of information for which the prediction measure is determined will be selected, or clicked on, by a user, if the item of the type of information is included in the search result. Without limitation, one such information type is news.

column12: ITQ-25, NEW CRYSTALLINE MICROPOROUS MATERIAL
column13: ITQ-25 (INSTITUTO DE TECNOLOG↕A QU↕MICA number 25) is a new crystalline microporous material with a framework of tetrahedral atoms connected by atoms capable of bridging the tetrahedral atoms, the tetrahedral atom framework being defined by the interconnections between the tetrahedrally coordinated atoms in its framework. ITQ-25 can be prepared in silicate compositions with a organic structure directing agent. It has a unique X-ray diffraction pattern, which identifies it as a new material. ITQ-25 is stable to calcination in air, absorbs hydrocarbons, and is catalytically active for hydrocarbon conversion.

column12: Perimeter Liquid-Cooled Electric Machine and Integrated Power Inverter
column13: A perimeter electric machine cooling arrangement includes a cooling conduit arranged to remove heat from an integrated housing containing an electric motor and a power inverter. The electrical connections between the electric motor and the power inverter are provided by flexible, pre-formed busbars that are arranged in pass over liquid cooling connections in the region between the electric motor and the power inverter. The integrated housing includes an intermediate cover over the electric motor and the power inverter portions of the housing, with a window through which the busbars can pass to reach the electric motor. The housing is further provided with an outer housing cover and seals that isolate the electric motor and the power inverter from the exterior environment and one another.

column12: FREMGANGSMAADE TIL SKAERING I BESTEMTE MATERIALER
column13: In accordance with the invention a method in wich N.C. machine is provided to cut sheet material like cloth, paper, cardboard, plastic, plywood, wood and similar chelt materials with a thickness of up to 15 mm. The raw material can be available in the roll form or in laminate planar form. <??>To feed material from the roll to the cutting area a motorized support is provided, in the way to prevent the material from stretching or being distorted before being cut in the table. <??>In order to have maximum througput from the machine, the cutting table is a conveyor made of an air and gas permeable material, and divided in three areas; feeding, cutting and removing area. Means are provided for the conveyor to prevent it to move during cutting time and to be moved by the X arm without changing the position to each other during feeding operation. <??>In each of the cutting and removing areas is an X-Y computer controlled assembly. In the cutting area a plasma jet cutter managed by the X-Y assembly in that way that is posible for the cutting beam to reach every point of the surface. The power suply and the tank for the gas to be transformed in plasma are in a stationary position and the beam path is conveniently protected. The lower side of the feeding and cutting area is covered by a cage from wich air is continuously removed in order to prevent motion of the material to be cut and in order to remove smoke and ofher products that result from the cutting process. Another motive for this cage is to provide means to disipate the energy of the plasma jet beam. <??>In the removing area is placed another X-Y computer controlled assembly with a head provided with a labelling and a suction device in order to automatically label and pick-up the cut parts and bring them to a storage area. <??>Since normally the minimum length of the marker necesary to make a complete suit is about 5 to 7 m., and, due to the simultaneity of the cutting and removing operation the lenght of the two areas must be the same, a machine to be able to cut the entire marker at once would result extremely long. To avoid the problem, the sistem we are dealing with is provided with a control to cut the marker by sections, normally named "windows" but, and this is very important, "variable windows" in order to cut the patterns falling completely into the cutting area. That is why here, is enough to have the length of the window a little bit bigger that the biggest part to be cut.

column12: COMPOSITION FOR THE DETECTION OF POSTPRANDIAL HYPERTRIGLYCERIDEMIA
column13: The invention relates to a composition of fatty acids, which can be used to detect moderate or severe postprandial hypertriglyceridemia in an individual and to determine an individual's capacity for metabolising postprandial triglycerides. The invention also relates to the method for obtaining data that can be used to detect moderate or severe postprandial hypertriglyceridemia in an individual and to the method for obtaining data that can be used to determine an individual's capacity for metabolising postprandial triglycerides, in which methods an individual's triglyceride level is determined at different times following the administration of the composition of the invention. Said methods can be used to identify individuals at risk of developing diseases such as metabolic syndrome, cardiovascular diseases, insulin resistance, atherosclerosis, etc., pathologies which are all associated with postprandial hypertriglyceridemia and a reduced capacity to metabolise fats.

column12: Refrigerator, such as fridge or freezer
column13: The refrigerator includes a casing determined by a wall with an internal covering (4), an external covering (3) and an intervening heat-insulating layer (2), through which wall is fed, via a penetration duct, a breather tube from the refrigerator storage space to the outside. The penetration duct has a first section (5) followed by a second section (7) separated by means of an intervening wall (6 or 6') which can be perforated or even removed. The first section (5) has a surrounding lip (11) which fits externally over the external insulation (3), while the second section (7), shaped internally as a truncated cone (8), is pressure-fitted onto a formation (9) of the internal covering (4), said formation (9) being provided with a seal (10) which can also be perforated or removed. The penetration duct is prepared to prevent the injection of the foam that is to constitute the heat-insulating layer (2), from reaching the outside or from penetrating into the refrigeration compartment of the corresponding refrigerator.

column12: PERIMETER LIQUID-COOLED ELECTRIC MACHINE AND INTEGRATED POWER INVERTER
column13: A perimeter electric machine cooling arrangement includes a cooling conduit arranged to remove heat from an integrated housing containing an electric motor and a power inverter. The electrical connections between the electric motor and the power inverter are provided by flexible, pre-formed busbars that are arranged in pass over liquid cooling connections in the region between the electric motor and the power inverter. The integrated housing includes an intermediate cover over the electric motor and the power inverter portions of the housing, with a window through which the busbars can pass to reach the electric motor. The housing is further provided with an outer housing cover and seals that isolate the electric motor and the power inverter from the exterior environment and one another.

column12: Locking piece assembly for latch bolts
column13: A locking piece assembly adapted for installation in a cylindrical lock and meant to engage a locking mechanism comprises a locking piece and a lock button. The locking piece has one end adapted to engage the locking mechanism and an opposite end with a connecting hook. The lock button has an aperture adapted for attachment to the locking piece connecting hook, and can be depressed to move the locking piece inward to engage the locking mechanism after the locking piece assembly is installed in the cylindrical lock. The lock button can be installed onto the locking piece by hand, specifically by inserting the connecting hook into the aperture on the lock button, pivoting the lock button with respect to the locking piece, and placing the locking piece and lock button into alignment. After installation, the connecting hook is held in place to prevent separation from the lock button aperture.

column12: Peg for overhead trouser conveyor
column13: A peg is provided for use in overhead conveyors for carrying trousers between work stations in an industrial pressing process. The body of the peg comprises an elongated rigid base having preferably two inverted V-shaped plates and twp strips secured thereto. An elongated rectangular prism, having two contact surfaces, is located within the legs of the inverted V-shaped plates and is secured by means of handles passing through each of the strips. A respective contact surface of the rectangular prism can be tilted from one of the legs of the inverted V-shaped plates to the other. A cylindrical rod is attached at one end to the rigid base by means that enable the rod and the peg body to rotate independently against each other. The other end of the rod is in the form of a hook which is connected to the overhead conveyor.

column12: FRONT-MOTOR-GENERATOR-SYSTEM UND HYBRIDELEKTROFAHRZEUG-BETRIEBSVERFAHREN
column13: Es werden ein System und ein Verfahren zur integrierten Elektrifizierung von Fahrzeugnebenaggregaten bereitgestellt, die üblicherweise von einem Verbrennungsmotor angetrieben werden, bei dem ein Elektromotor an einen gemeinsamen Nebenaggregatantrieb gekoppelt ist, der eine Vielzahl von Nebenaggregaten antreibt, wie etwa eine Servolenkungspumpe, einen Klimakompressor, einen Luftkompressor, eine thermodynamische Heizvorrichtung und/oder eine Kühlmittelpumpe. Bei der integrierten elektrifizierten Nebenaggregateinheit sind vorzugsweise der Elektromotor, der Nebenaggregatantrieb und die Nebenaggregate in einem gemeinsamen Gehäuse angeordnet, das dazu konfiguriert ist, an einem Fahrgestelllängsträger des Fahrzeugs montiert zu werden, wobei das gemeinsame Gehäuse Wanddurchführungen beinhaltet, die eine schnelle Verbindung der Nebenaggregate mit externen Leitungen des Fahrzeugs erleichtern.
